f=Engineering/aegis/operational/skill/aegis-skill-routing.md · p=aegis's skills fit together. aegis department's **defensive** security agent: maps what wrong, finds has, reviews risky changes adversarially, verifies fixes actually close. cypher (the caged adversary, built) offensive half; aegis defends. aegis coordinates fixes; builders' code. · h2:The shape=`marketplace/threat-model (the map — what could go wrong, who, what to do) \· │ scopes \· ▼ \· vuln-pipeline (breadth: recon→find→verify→dedupe→triage→route)  ◄── ops CVE handoff \· │                                                        ◄── cypher findings (via quinn)` · h2:Routing rules="What wrong map attack surface threat model" **marketplace/threat-model** (aegis decides build/refresh; imported skill produces it)., "Scan find vulns triage findings" **vuln-pipeline** (threat-model-scoped; static first, execution sandbox)., "Security-review diff safe" (usually dev's routing) **secure-code-review**., "Patch verify fix closed" **verified-patching** (four checks, closed)., Execution any target code quinn's sandbox (Rail 2); fail closed outside departmental override. · h2:Handoffs=**dev**: risky diffs route (code-review-standards); findings route owning builders; new dependency risk flagged; aegis never edits builders' code, coordinates., **quinn**: aegis's S-tier verdicts feed release gate; sandbox quinn's; closed finding writes regression-map entry; cypher findings arrive quinn's intake., **cypher** (adversary, built): runs verified-patching's check independently (Rail caged); re-attacks trustworthy version "can't re-break." Until built, aegis self-checks, labeled., **ops**: CVE handoff maintenance-hygiene (above patch-level joint); data-touching fixes ops-sequenced, operator-run (Rail 3)., **AI Agents dept (future)**: LLM-specific attack classes (prompt injection, tool poisoning) overlap; coordinate build (plan §6)., Senior authority: **Security Charter** aegis enforces Rails (sandbox) (no agent data writes) itself; operator amends.